data: In the fictional town of Lagros, the idealistic new Mayor faces some very real problems. Mayor Joseph Santiago discovers a bunch of wayward employees have turned the municipal hall into a boarding house and, worse, have been making under the table deals at every turn. His efforts to fight corruption–both petty and large scale-are blocked by a political dynasty led by Governor Antonio Rubio and Congressman Anton Rubio.

The episode unveils Mayor Joseph Santiago's past-he saw his father murdered on the streets of Lagros. His father was a journalist and newspaper publisher who exposed wrongdoings in the province. The episode also digs deeper into the psyche of Governor Antonio Rubio, who has found creative ways to earn from every local government project, whether road and bridge construction or furniture supplies in the capitol.

Fate brings Mayor Joseph Santiago back to his old elementary school where the opposite of progress has taken effect. He encounters sluggish, malnourished students who have to use umbrellas inside their leaking classrooms and finds that several grades are being taught in the same room and at the same time by just one teacher! The Mayor brings up the sorry state of the province's public schools during a forum attended by Governor Antonio Rubio, causing the tension between them to take a very nasty turn. In the meantime, the Mayor's Chief of Staff, Karen very literally falls for the young Congressman Anton Rubio.

Change has begun in the town of Lagros. After almost a year in office, Mayor Joseph Santiago's projects are flourishing, bringing in nominations, awards and national attention for the very first time. But investors continue to move slowly despite the signs of progress. It is revealed that the Governor's requests for huge kickbacks are turning businessmen off in droves. The town's biggest industry continues to be illegal logging. At the helm of it is the Governor's mistress Eliza Bauer, who managed to claw her way out of poverty and become a powerful contractor and furniture exporter. When the denuded forests of the province become national news, all hell breaks loose.

A decade of wanton and illegal logging leaves the watersheds of Sibilan vulnerable when a major storm hits. The result: a massive flash flood, causing the death of hundreds of civilians. How Mayor Joseph Santiago and his staff respond to the disaster, even with their own families in danger, paints a moving picture of what political leadership can be. The finale episode shows the long term impact of corruption and the drastic need for elected officials to step up and practice good governance.

data: [I_Know_What_You_Did_Last_Summer_(The_Vampire_Diaries)|I Know What You Did Last Summer]

With her relationship with Damon still intact, Elena starts school with Caroline at Whitmore College, excited about the chance to have a normal college experience, but their good time ends badly when their roommate is brutally murdered by what seems to be another vampire there. Damon is left to take care of Jeremy, who has trouble adjusting back into school after telling everyone he faked his own death. Bonnie, still dead doesn't want anyone to know that she is dead and has Jeremy masquerade as her. Katherine has trouble adjusting to being human again and needs Damon's help after Silas comes after her and also her other enemies who are after her as she is vulnerable. Matt says goodbye to Rebekah and runs into an old friend named Nadia. Stefan is still in the locker underwater and is hallucinating while fighting the urge to turn off his humanity.

Underwater, Stefan has hallucinations of Damon telling him to turn off his humanity in order to get out. At Whitmore, Elena and Caroline try to figure out how Megan knew Elena's father and why her murder was covered up by the school and look into a mysterious professor. Jeremy and Matt go on the run with Katherine with Silas on their tail. Caroline bonds with Jesse over their bad relationships. Elena, under the control of Silas, ties Damon up and attempts to kill him, but returns to normal before doing so. She finds out the truth about Stefan and temporarily drops out of college to go look for him. Elena tells Damon that even though Stefan will be there she will still love him. Elena, Damon and Sheriff Forbes find Stefan's safe, but instead of Stefan, they find a dead body, meaning Stefan was very hungry and could have turned off his humanity.

Stefan finally comes back to life after three months being locked in a cage under the water. When Elena tells Damon that she had a dream about Stefan in a bar, Katherine says she had them too. Damon and Elena, alongside Katherine go to a bar to search for Stefan where they find the waitress who was bitten by Stefan. Quetsia has Stefan hostage as she reveals her plans of destroying Silas by using Stefan to make him weaker. Meanwhile, Nadia uses Matt to contact Edward and uses him to get information about Katherine. Nadia kidnaps Katherine and goes to Silas to give her but she realizes that he is using her. When Damon finds Stefan, Quetsia reveals him that Stefan and Elena are destined as she reveals information about her and Silas in the past. Finally when Stefan awakes following Quetsia's spell, he starts suffering from amnesia.

When Damon tries to remind Stefan about him and his past, Stefan has a problem with restraining. While Elena tries to remember Stefan about how they met and their past, Matt looks for help from Jeremy. Meanwhile, Jeremy is forced to tell Damon the truth about Bonnie. When Elena finally convinces Stefan to restain himself, he tries to kiss her but she rejects. Elena tells him that she's with Damon, which makes Stefan jealous. With all of this Stefan decides to turn his humanity off and become a ripper again, going to the graveyard where he meets Caroline and Jesse and ends up attacking Jesse. Elena finally learns that Bonnie is dead when Damon is forced to tell her. After he meets Caroline, Stefan is able to control himself. Tyler returns when Damon, Elena, Caroline, Matt and Jeremy are honouring Bonnie's death. Wes realizes that Jesse has vampire blood in his system and he is on a mission to make him a new vampire.

data: Australia and New Zealand as per AS/NZS 3000:2007 Figure 3.2 (or as per IEC 60446 as approved by AS:3000)

Red (or brown) In Australia and New Zealand, active conductors can be any color except green/yellow, green, yellow, black or light blue. Yellow is no longer permitted in the 2007 revision of wiring code ASNZS 3000. European color codes are used for all IEC or flex cables such as extension leads, appliance leads etc. and are equally permitted for use in building wiring per AS/NZS 3000:2007.
Green/yellow striped (green on very old installations)
UK until April 2006, Hong Kong until April 2009, South Africa, Malaysia, Singapore until February 2011
Green/yellow striped (green on installations before c. 1970)
Former USSR (Russia, Ukraine, Kazakhstan) and People's Republic of China (per GB 50303-2002 Section 15.2.2)
Yellow/green striped, older may be only yellow or bare copper
United States (common practice) See Paul Cook: Harmonised colours and alphanumeric marking. IEE Wiring Matters, Spring 2006.

United States (alternative practice) Since 1975, the U.S. National Electric Code has not specified coloring of phase conductors. It is common practice in many regions to identify 120/208Y conductors as black, red, and blue. Local regulations may amend the N.E.C. The U.S. National Electric Code has color requirements for grounded conductors, ground and grounded-delta 3-phase systems which result in one ungrounded leg having a higher voltage potential to ground than the other two ungrounded legs. Orange is only appropriate when the system has a grounded delta service, regardless of voltage.

table-1254-735.caption: Steam locomotives
data: BR lined green with late crest

Built 1956. Boiler was lifted during summer 2009. Welding of copper plates for the new firebox have been done. Work will begin in earnest when the Bridge & Wheels appeal nears £1million. Expected back in service 2015.
BR lined black with late crest
Built in 1959. Purchased by the railway from private owner. Returned to service in 2013 following a 1 year overhaul.
BR lined green with late crest
BR lined green with late crest
BR lined black with early crest

Built 1957. Withdrawn early due to cracked cylinder. Loco now in store awaiting cylinder fabrication to become complete. Out of service for approx 30 months. Currently having a mid life boiler overhaul and is expected back in service by late 2013.
BR lined black with late crest
Built 1937. Returned to service in 2010 after a lengthy overhaul.
BR unlined black with late crest
BR lined blue with early crest
Built 1937. Re-entered service in 2006. Recently returned to service following firebox repairs.

Built 1927. Several parts of the locomotive are from sister engine, S15 number 30841. Previously certified for Whitby-Battersby running but since firebox repairs in June–July 2010, restricted to regular NYMR services. Boiler ticket expired in July 2013.

Built 1927. Awaiting restoration with a view to swapping the boiler onto 825 when that locomotive's certificate runs out in 2013 so that it can be fast-tracked back into service. However as a condition of sale will make sure it will be eventually restored as 830.
Built in 1936. Original frames found to be out of line. Many of the locomotive's components can be found in use on 30825 (825). Now essentially scrapped.
Built 1950. Components for the boiler are mostly in hand. Due back into service in 2014.
Built in 1940. Chassis currently stored at Grosmont.
Built 1943. In store at Grosmont awaiting heavy overhaul, having been the railway's workhorse throughout much of the 1990s.
BR lined black with early crest
Built 1947. Arrived in December 2012 following overhaul. Boiler ticket expires in 2022. Currently painted to represent classmate 61002 "Impala".

data: While the Telemark Battalion currently is fully professional, the 2012 White Paper proposes including some conscripts. The battalion is the Army's rapid reaction force. The battalion is equipped with CV-90 infantry fighting vehicles and Leopard 2 tanks, and can be deployed quickly to deal with national or international crises.
The 2nd Battalion is equipped with lightly armored vehicles. It is mainly based on conscript troops
The Engineer Battalion secures the Army's mobility. The battalion also conducts ferry-operations and provides the Army's NRBC defense capability.

The Intelligence Battalion is responsible for the intelligence-support to military operations. Although the unit is part of Brigade Nord, it is capable to support all branches of the Norwegian Defense Forces.
The Signals Battalion operates the brigade's communications.
The Combat Service and Support battalion is the Army's transportation and supply unit. The battalion also provides maintenance services.

data: Gold mining season begins in Dawson City, Yukon, and the countdown to winter is on. Newcomer Big Al worries his season could be over before it starts when his excavator named ‘Big Girl’ fails. Further south, Bernie struggles not only to teach his young sons how to be miners, but also to find gold. In Moose Creek, best friends Ken and Guillaume cannot get their sluice machine “The Beast” up and running – and without it, their entire season could be a bust.

It is week three for mining crew Ken and Guillaume and non-stop rain jeopardizes their cut. On Sulphur Creek, young crew boss Karl has no sluice machine, and no sluicer means no gold. Karl’s father Marty, a highly respected self-made miner, builds a new one from scratch. While Karl waits, he struggles to keep his crew on task – and live up to his father’s high expectations.
